
[1]pernicious

   PERNI'CIOUS, a. [L. perniciosus, from pernicies; perneco, to kill; per
   and nex, necis,death.]

   1. Destructive; having the quality of killing, destroying or injuring;
   very injurious or mischievous. Food, drink or air may be pernicious to
   life or health.

   2. Destructive; tending to injure or destroy. Evil examples are
   pernicious to morals. Intemperance is a pernicious vice.

   3. [L. pernix.] Quick. [Not used.]
